{
  "action_id": "1654",
  "action_title": "Cut and apply herbicide to control bracken",
  "key_messages": "Key Messages:\n\nOne randomized, controlled study in the UK\u00a0found that cutting and applying herbicide to control bracken did not alter heather biomass. One randomized, controlled, before-and-after trial in Norway\u00a0found that cutting and applying herbicide increased heather cover. One\u00a0randomized, replicated, controlled, paired study in the UK found that cutting and using herbicide had no significant effect on the cover of seven plant species.\nOne replicated, randomized, controlled study in the UK\u00a0found that cutting bracken followed by applying herbicide increased plant species richness when compared with applying herbicide followed by cutting.\nThree randomized, controlled studies (one also a before-and-after trial, and one of which was a paired study) in the UK\u00a0and Norway\u00a0found that cutting and applying herbicide reduced bracken biomass\u00a0or cover."
}

{
  "query": "When trying to control bracken in UK heathlands, how does using herbicide alone compare to cutting, or a combination of both?",
  "relevant_summary": "Across UK studies, applying herbicide alone generally reduced bracken biomass or cover, though one study found no change, and effects on heather and other vegetation were mixed: heather seedlings or biomass sometimes increased, but two studies reported no increase in heather cover; plant species richness increased at one heathland but showed no effect at another; some grasses and gorse increased (1652). Cutting alone similarly tended to reduce bracken biomass or cover in several UK studies, but results were mixed in others, including one study with no decrease; effects on heather were variable, with some studies showing increased biomass and others no increase in cover or seedlings; species richness increased in one study and diversity increased without a richness change in another; certain grasses increased while gorse and cow-wheat did not (1653). Combining cutting with herbicide reduced bracken biomass or cover in UK studies; UK evidence reported no change in heather biomass and no significant effect on the cover of seven plant species, while a UK trial found species richness increased when cutting preceded herbicide compared to the reverse sequence (1654).",
  "action_ids": [
    "1652",
    "1653",
    "1654"
  ]
}

